&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&quot;description&quot;&gt;Description&lt;&#x2F;h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The requirements were simple: build a contraption that simulates a satellite moving on its orbital path at different elevations.
This was a summer break project and the time was therefore limited.
Just two months to figure out a concept, do the design, manufacture the parts, assemble, test and tune the system to have it ready for the upcoming open day of the university.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The concept environed a U-shaped rail with a tilting mechanism to change the elevation of the orbit.
A carriage would need to move on that rail to simulate the &#x27;satellite&#x27; on its orbital track.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This ultimately led to the modular &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;krepa098.github.io&#x2F;projects&#x2F;galileo-orbit-mockup&#x2F;#p3&quot;&gt;[laser-cut]&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; construction made from several arc segments forming a semicircle.
A belt was driven along the arc by a small stepper motor and &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;krepa098.github.io&#x2F;projects&#x2F;galileo-orbit-mockup&#x2F;#p6&quot;&gt;[its two-stage gearbox]&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; (inspired by cable lifts), that &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;krepa098.github.io&#x2F;projects&#x2F;galileo-orbit-mockup&#x2F;#p7&quot;&gt;[dragged the carriage]&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; along with it.
Steel counterweights at each end kept the torque required to change the orbit&#x27;s elevation to a minimum.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Underneath the carriage, an &lt;code&gt;ArUco&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; served as a target for the ground station to track.
The position of the marker was extracted with &lt;code&gt;OpenCV&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; and a simple PID loop ensured smooth tracking.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lastly, a &lt;code&gt;Qt&#x2F;QML&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;krepa098.github.io&#x2F;projects&#x2F;galileo-orbit-mockup&#x2F;#p2&quot;&gt;[interface]&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; was added to give guests the possibility to take manual control over the antenna and the orbit.
It also served as a convenient interface to tweak the gains of the PID loop.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This project was exhibited during several open days until receiving significant damage during transport.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
